<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Step Wedge" class="currentChild" href="Step_Wedge">Step Wedge</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A film positive or negative comprising lines of type at various sizes—some at hard-to-reproduce sizes—used to determine the exposure time for <a title="Photostencil" href="Photostencil">photostencil</a>s used in <a title="Screen Printing" href="Screen_Printing">screen printing</a>. By covering various portions of the step wedge and exposing portions of it for varying amounts of time, upon development, washing, and mounting the best exposure time for a particular photostencil material can be gauged. See <a title="Photostencil" href="Photostencil">Photostencil</a>. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
A <em>step wedge</em> is also an alternate term for a type of <a title="Gray Scale" href="Gray_Scale">gray scale</a> known as a <a title="Step Tablet" href="Step_Tablet">step tablet</a>. See <a title="Step Tablet" href="Step_Tablet">Step Tablet</a> and <a title="Gray Scale" href="Gray_Scale">Gray Scale</a>. 
</p>
